Actually, it's not.  Salash is 100% correct imo.  When you hand the last 4 pieces in, you don't get a scroll of Summon: Uberpet... you get Summon: Orb.   The orb(with it's 20int, 100 mana, 50 resist points, etc.) is the epic... it just happens to have one charge of a VERY nice pet on it. <br>
<br>
Look at the big picture:  The effect on druid and necro epics are 100% useless on large encounters, and only moderately useful in normal ones.  Warrior/ranger/rogue epic weapons are bested by some of the Velious stuff, and can end up backpacked in the larger guilds.  <br>
<br>
Mages, however, get an unparalleled held item, with an effect that's incredibly useful about 90% of the time... only time it's not is on fire encounters(Rak'Ashiir, etc.), posion(Trak, Severilous, etc.), and bad pathing areas.   The only time I could <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ever</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> imagine taking the Orb off my mage(if I ever get it) would be in favor of a Zlandicar heart when I needed regen... and people with both of those items aren't exactly common.  We should be glad that it's as useful as it is, and stop complaining.  <p><hr width=325 align=LEFT><font color=007100><b>Mathas Oakheart</b></font> - 60th Hierophant, Bristlebane<br><font color=0000AE><b>Malkar Zauviir</b></font> - 49th Magician, Bristlebane<br><hr width=325 align=LEFT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#333333>(6/7/01 7:27:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: whats the point</span><hr size=1> It also depends on your guild. I can use a pet on any PoH and PoF raid cause my guild trusts me.  There are times where I decide its not worth the risk anyways, part of why they trust me.  In chardok, I never use a pet except in the King and queen fights, and then I don't start summoning till the pull/charge cause of the AoEs, the zone just doesn't accomidate pets well.  Chardok is really the only place that comes to mind where I don't use a pet.  Couple islands on PoA and in HoT I summon after the pull again due to AoEs.  It took many petless raids before I could use pets at my discression.  My advice is to talk to whoever leads the raids, and the enchanters, and also group with them so they can see that you are good with pets, and mostly, give it time.<br>
<br>
